alt_text: Green River in the Flaming Gorge National Recreation Area
description: The family of Dr. Melinda Poyer often make a six-hour-long rafting trip on the Green River in the Flaming Gorge National Recreation Area where her kids Kevin, 14, left, and Ryan, 16, right, handle the paddling. She moved west with her husband and six kids, ages 3 through 16, in December of 2006 to find a better quality of life compared to what was possible in Florida. The family of outdoor enthusiasts had planned to someday retire to Wyoming, but moved up their schedule so that the kids could enjoy the benefits of living in the high deserts' wide open spaces. They have a home on the north side of Rock Springs.

name: Longwoodrose.jpg
description: The rose beds at Longwood Gardens in Kennett Square, Pa., date back to the 1930s, as do many of the gardens here. The intoxicating fragrances of hundreds of roses fill the garden from June to October.

name: Rockefellerrose.jpg
description: The Peggy Rockefeller Rose Garden draws thousands of visitors, especially between May and October when more than 650 varieties of roses are in peak bloom.

name: Lyndalerose.jpg
description: Nestled between a Lake Harriet and the Roberts Bird Sanctuary in Minneapolis, Minn., is the Lyndale Park Rose Garden. This is the second-oldest public rose garden in the U.S.

name: Huntingtonrose_edited-1.jpg
description: This 3-acre rose garden at The Huntington complex in San Marino, Calif., contains more than 3,000 individual plants and more than 1,200 different varieties of flowers. It is enjoyed by thousands of visitors each year.

name: tylerrose.jpg
description: The Tyler Municipal Rose Garden is the largest public garden in the country. Rose growers in Tyler produce 60 percent of the nation's commercially grown roses.

name: McGillrose.jpg
description: The McGill Rose Garden in Charlotte, N.C., was originally a coal yard until the wife of the yard owner planted a pair of rose bushes. Today, it serves as a landmark in the city's First Ward and hosts numerous weddings throughout the year.

name: krasbergrose2.jpg
description: Krasberg Rose Garden in Chicago features more than 5,000 roses, which typically bloom between May and October. Within this 3-acre garden is a true-red tea rose that can reach 6 feet. A large fountain framed by rose beds beckons children to come in and splash around.

name: Dergootrose.jpg
description: Originally a working farm, the Rudolf W. van der Goot Rose Garden holds more than 3,000 roses of 325 varieties. A popular location for wedding photography, the rose garden is part of an extensive arboretum that includes an ornamental grass collection, shrubs and perennials.

name: Portlandrose.jpg
description: Constructed in 1918, the Portland International Rose Test Garden is considered the largest rose test garden in the country. The expansive garden is a testing ground for around 200 rose cultivars each year.

name: Elizabeth_rose_garden_2.jpg
description: Located in Hartford, Conn., the Elizabeth Rose Garden is considered the oldest municipal rose garden in the country. It features a heritage area with "antique" roses on display.

name: kelleherrose.jpg
description: Many Bostonians call the Kelleher Rose Garden a "secret garden" because it's hidden from view by tall evergreen hedges. Those who find the entrance are treated to a variety of rose bushes and plants that create a romantic atmosphere in the Fenway area.

name: Municipalrose.jpg
description: Located in Loose Park, the Laura Conyers Smith Municipal Rose Garden contains 3,000 plants of 150 different varieties. Hundreds of couples hold weddings in the garden each year, and thousands of photographers come here to snap photos of colorful flowers.
